subproject.description: This project aims to promote knowledge and awareness in Human Development in oPt.  The present project is part of a multi-phased programme designed for advocacy in oPt which will lead to the production of the National Human Development Report, advocacy for human development, capacity building of institutions including universities, NGOs, the media and policy making institutions. The programme will lead to capacity building for identifying priorities for policy, analysing emerging trends, collecting and processing data, and advocating for human development. It has as its main goal the promotion of national dialogue, capacity building, and identification of development alternatives that impact human development in oPt.  The NHDR project will be implemented in two phases. The first phase involves the preparation of the NHDR itself. The second phase will cover the capacity building, advocacy, networking, and the production of Human Development materials.
